Package com.example.eventlottery.Models

Class EventModel

java.lang.Object
com.example.eventlottery.Models.EventModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class EventModel extends Object implements Serializable
Event Model This class represent an event where user can join/unjoin to the waitlist, and be selected by a lottery system so they can enroll in the event Also this class has all the information of the event, it include it deadlines, if geolocation is available or not It also contains the facility that the event belong

      public EventModel(String facilityID, Boolean geolocationRequired, Integer waitingListLimit, Integer capacity, Date joinDeadline, String eventStrLocation, String eventTitle, String eventDescription, String organizer)
      Constructor with parameters, when the event is already created and we need to grab the event information from firebase
      Parameters:
      facilityID - The facility ID of the event
      geolocationRequired - Whether geolocation is required for the event
      waitingListLimit - The waiting list limit of the event
      capacity - The capacity of the event
      joinDeadline - The deadline for joining the event
      eventStrLocation - The location of the event
      eventTitle - The title of the event
      eventDescription - The description of the event
      organizer - The organizer of the event

    • EventModel

      Constructor with parameters, when the event is already created and we need to grab the event information from firebase
      Parameters:
      facilityID - The facility ID of the event
      eventID - The event ID of the event. Calling the above constructor and setting event ID in this constructor
      geolocationRequired - Whether geolocation is required for the event
      waitingListLimit - The waiting list limit of the event
      capacity - The capacity of the event
      joinDeadline - The deadline for joining the event

      organizer - The organizer of the event
